docs.abstract: Good will between New York City labor unions and Mayor Bill de Blasio is threatened by several overlapping state and federal fund-raising investigations bringing unwanted scrutiny and potential problems; de Blasio’s approval numbers are below 50 percent and city’s powerful public and private unions are beginning to consider whether to stick with an embattled mayor in 2017 re-election bid or risk abandoning their long-time supporter to back a challenger.
